‚úÖ Why your old code didn‚Äôt work for Gujarati

PyPDF2 has very weak support for non-English languages (Gujarati, Hindi, Tamil, etc.).
Most Indian-language PDFs use embedded fonts, and PyPDF2 fails to extract that text correctly.

‚úÖ Best solution: Use pdfplumber (works MUCH better for Gujarati)

pdfplumber extracts Unicode text properly.

‚úîÔ∏è Updated Working Code (Gujarati + English + Numbers)
Install required library

Open terminal / CMD:

pip install pdfplumber

‚ú® Final Python Script
import os
import pdfplumber

def search_pdf_folder(folder_path, keyword):
    keyword = keyword.lower()
    found_files = []

    for filename in os.listdir(folder_path):
        if filename.endswith(".pdf"):
            pdf_path = os.path.join(folder_path, filename)
            try:
                with pdfplumber.open(pdf_path) as pdf:
                    for page in pdf.pages:
                        text = page.extract_text()
                        if text and keyword in text.lower():
                            found_files.append(filename)
                            break
            except Exception as e:
                print(f"Could not read {filename}: {e}")

    return found_files


if __name__ == "__main__":
    folder = input("Enter the folder path: ")
    word = input("Enter the word to search: ")

    print("\nSearching... Please wait...\n")

    results = search_pdf_folder(folder, word)

    if results:
        print("Word found in these PDF files:\n")
        for file in results:
            print(" -", file)
    else:
        print("No PDF contains this word.")

